彼得原理

The Peter Principle

关键信息

Key information

  • 名称：彼得原理。
  • Name: the Peter Principle.
  • 用途：人力资源和绩效管理，开发人力潜能。
  • Uses: human resource and performance management, development of human potential.
  • 它为什么会成功？它的成功是不确定的，因为它取决于个人和组织。
  • Why is it successful? Its success is uncertain because it depends on the individuals and the organisations.
  • 关键词：
    • 能力：在特定岗位上实现最高效率所需的知识和技能
    • 效率：卓越的代名词，员工利用有限的资源（时间、金钱等）完成某些任务的能力
    • 等级制度：组织内的权力结构
    • 晋升：在组织内任命一名员工到更高级别。
  • Key words:
    • Competence: knowledge and know-how required for maximum efficiency in a given position
    • Efficiency: synonymous with excellence, the ability of an employee to perform certain tasks with limited resources (time, money, etc.)
    • Hierarchy: authority structure within an organisation
    • Promotion: appointing a worker to a higher level within an organisation.

介绍

Introduction

在思考彼得原理时，尤其需要意识到的是，尽管该模型在许多特定情况下具有启发性，但它出自一本讽刺小说，因此在建立科学事实时必须谨慎使用。在组织内部等级制度日益强化的背景下，内部晋升的问题凸显出来。员工的能力是否应该成为决定晋升的主要标准？如何衡量这种能力水平？高效的员工是否必然会成为优秀的组织者？

When considering the Peter Principle, it is particularly important to realise that this model, though enlightening in many given situations, comes from a satirical book and, therefore, must be used with caution to when establishing scientific facts. In the context of increasingly strong hierarchies within organisations, there is the question of internal promotion. Should the competence of an employee be the dominant criterion for determining hierarchical ascension? How can this level of competence be measured? Does an efficient employee necessarily make for a good organiser?

模型定义

Definition of the model

彼得原理指出，如果一名员工在某个层级工作高效，他就会升职到更高的层级，以此类推，直到达到效率最低的层级。如果他无法被降职，这意味着所有组织结构都会自然地朝着效率更低的方向发展。

The Peter Principle states that if an employee is working efficiently at a given hierarchical level, he will be promoted to the next level above and so on, until he reaches the level where he is inefficient. If he cannot be demoted, this means that all structures naturally evolve towards a balance of greater inefficiency.

虽然乍一看，这个原则似乎有些荒谬，但它确实提出了一些人力资源管理方面的问题。为了个人和公司的利益，谁应该被提拔？为了提高整体效率，应该在什么条件下这样做？

Although, at first glance, the principle may seem absurd, it does raise some issues regarding human resource management. Who should be promoted for the good of both the individual and the company? And under what conditions should this be done in order to increase overall efficiency?

理论

Theory

劳伦斯·约翰逊·彼得（加拿大教育家、心理学家，1919-1990）

Laurence Johnson Peter (Canadian educator and psychologist, 1919-1990)

劳伦斯·J·彼得，原籍温哥华，1958年从西华盛顿州立学院毕业后，迅速成为一名教师，同时继续攻读心理学和教育科学，并于1963年获得博士学位。随后，他担任伊芙琳·弗里登中心主任，并于1966年担任南加州大学遇到困难的项目的顾问。

After graduating in 1958 from Western Washington State College, Laurence J. Peter, originally from Vancouver, quickly became a teacher while pursuing studies in psychology and education sciences, in which he obtained a doctorate degree in 1963. He then directed the Evelyn Frieden Center and acted as an adviser for programs that experienced difficulties at the University of Southern California in 1966.

他的第一本书《规范性教学》于 1965 年出版，但直到与雷蒙德·赫尔（加拿大作家，1919-1985 年）合作出版《彼得原理》（1969 年）后，他才广为人知。

His first book, Prescriptive Teaching, was published in 1965 but it was not until the publication of The Peter Principle (1969), written in collaboration with Raymond Hull (Canadian writer, 1919-1985), that he became well-known.

彼得原理的假设

The hypotheses of the Peter Principle

与所有经济模型一样，彼得原理也基于一些值得研究的假设。如果我们只看最重要的假设，这些假设包括（但不限于）：

The Peter Principle, like all economic models, is based on hypotheses that are useful to investigate. If we only look at the most important, these include (but are not limited to):

  • 公司的层级结构自然呈现金字塔形。这个简化的视图展现了严格划分的层级：基层员工由少数几位经理领导，而这些经理又由更少的高级主管管理，如此循环往复。
  • The hierarchical structure of a company is naturally in the form of a pyramid. This simplified view shows the strictly defined hierarchical levels: basic workers are led by a few managers, who are themselves managed by even fewer superior executives and so on.

  • 工作岗位是固定的，包含固定的任务：被分配到某个岗位的员工必须完成一定数量的任务。如果他未能完成预期的工作，该岗位就无法完成。如果他完成了，就不会被分配其他任务。然而，需要注意的是，这些结构性描述可以追溯到某个时期，而如今的公司组织更加灵活，例如，他们以项目或网络为单位开展工作。
  • Working positions are rigid and include set tasks: the worker assigned to a position performs a certain number of tasks. If he fails to do the work expected, it will simply not get done. If he succeeds, he will not be given other tasks. In this regard, however, note that these structural descriptions date back to a certain time and companies are currently much more flexible organisations that work from a project or network, for example.
  • 最有力且最具争议的假设是书中提到的“彼得假设”。较高层级职位所需的能力水平与较低层级职位所需的能力完全无关。如果一名员工最适合某个职位，并被提拔到更高的级别，那么他晋升后的能力水平完全不可预测。
  • The strongest and most controversial hypothesis is what the book refers to as the ‘Peter hypothesis’. The level of competence required for a higher hierarchical position is completely independent of the competence required for a hierarchically inferior position. If an employee is the most suitable for a position and is promoted to a higher level, his level of competence after that promotion is completely unpredictable.

根据 Jean-Paul Delahaye（法国计算机科学家和数学家，生于 1952 年）的说法，如果我们接受这些简单的假设，那么我们在逻辑上可以假设所有晋升都有可能降低员工的绩效，原因有两个：

According to Jean-Paul Delahaye (French computer scientist and mathematician, born in 1952), if we accept these simplistic assumptions, we are logically assuming that all promotions have a tendency to reduce an employee’s performance due to two effects:

  • 棘轮效应：员工无法回溯，因为无法降职。如果员工竞争心强，他就会继续向上爬，而不会停留在自己高效的职位上。这种上升趋势会持续下去，直到他达到一个过高的级别，不再高效。然后，员工就会被困在这个级别，无法降职，也无法继续晋升。
  • The ratchet effect: backtracking is impossible as an employee cannot be demoted. If he is competitive, he will continue to climb the ladder and will not remain in a position where he is efficient. The movement will effectively continue until he reaches a level that is too high, in which he is no longer efficient. The employee is then stuck at this level and cannot be demoted nor continue to rise.
  • 回归平均值的统计效应（统计分布原理）：在随机的“正常”事件中，获得接近平均值的结果的概率高于获得非常高或非常低的结果。因此，如果公司有幸拥有一位能力远超平均水平的员工，并决定更换其职位，那么这又一次决定了这位员工的能力是否很有可能达到平均水平。
  • The statistical effect of regressing towards the average (of the principle of statistical distribution): during a random, ‘normal’ event, the probability of achieving a result close to average is higher than getting a very high or very low result. Thus, the company, which is fortunate enough to be able to count on an employee that is well above average competency and decides to change their position, once again determines the competence of the employee with a good chance of achieving an average result.

彼得原理假设的背后隐藏着一个难以忽视的真相：随着时间的推移，每个职位越来越可能被不称职的员工占据，而职位在层级结构中的位置越高，其对整体绩效就越重要。这并不意味着金字塔的底层对企业正常运转的重要性不如顶层，事实上恰恰相反。简而言之，如果我们接受金字塔结构并同等重视每个层级，那么当该层级中的职位较少时，该职位对整体绩效的重要性就会更高。例如，如果有两名经理负责五名员工，那么经理的个人能力占其层级绩效的 50%，而每个员工的个人绩效仅占 20%。

Behind the hypotheses of the Peter Principle lies an inconvenient truth: over time, each position is increasingly likely to be occupied by an incompetent employee, while the higher up a position is in the hierarchy, the more important it is to the overall performance of the structure. This does not mean that the base of the pyramid is any less essential to the proper functioning of the business than the top, it is in fact the reverse. Put simply, if we accept the pyramid structure and place equal emphasis on each level, a position has more importance for the overall performance when there are fewer positions within that level. For example, if there are two managers for five employees, the individual competence of the manager accounts for 50% of the performance of its hierarchical level, while the individual performance of each employee only accounts for 20%.

在彼得原理的假设中，特别是棘轮效应的假设中，似乎很清楚“每个员工都倾向于升到他无法胜任的水平”，因此结构的自然平衡是每个职位都由无法承担责任的人占据。

In the hypotheses of the Peter Principle, particularly that of the ratchet effect, it seems clear that ‘every employee tends to rise to his level of incompetence’, so that the natural balance of a structure is that each position is occupied by someone who cannot bear the responsibilities.

不称职的员工

The incompetent employees

这一原则由劳伦斯·J·彼得 (Laurence J. Peter) 提出，是组织完整科学的一部分，他称之为“等级学”。

This principle was conceived by Laurence J. Peter as part of a complete science of organisations that he called ‘hierarchiology’.

这篇论文旨在提供具体的应用，并将他的模型与他观察到的组织现实进行对比。当然，他也指出了该原则的例外情况。例如，最有能力的员工并不总是能得到晋升。他列举了一些不称职员工获得晋升的案例，并解释了原因。

This seeks to provide concrete applications and confronts his model with the reality of the organisations that he observed. Of course, he notes exceptions to the principle. For example, the most competent are not always promoted. He highlights several cases where incompetent employees are promoted and explains why.

  • 强力升华或伪发展：这种策略会将不称职的员工提拔到更高层级，其主要目的是维持所有其他人的希望，让他们相信自己有一天也能获得晋升。这种策略很危险，因为对于那些不属于层级的人来说，这只是一种幻觉。
  • Powerful sublimation or pseudo-development: this strategy, which promotes an incompetent employee to an upper level, mainly serves to maintain the hope of all others who believe they may also be promoted one day. This is dangerous because it is just an illusion for people who are not part of the hierarchy.
  • 横向晋升：将不称职的员工提拔到一个新的、无用的职位，并赋予其更高的头衔，以限制其在现任职位上可能造成的损害。
  • Lateral arabesque: this promotes an incompetent employee to a new, useless position with a grander title to limit the damage he may cause in his current position.
  • 彼得逆转：在这种情况下，不称职员工的晋升是因为他们遵守了上级规定的标准，而不是他们的效率。最终效果和手段是相反的，因为标准的存在是为了提高生产力，而遵守标准的价值与提高生产力的价值是同等的。
  • Peter reversal: in this case, the promotion of an incompetent employee is due to their compliance with standards imposed by the hierarchy rather than their efficiency. The end effect and means are reversed, since the standards exist to increase productivity and give as much value to compliance of standards as to productivity.
  • 等级分明：为了避免员工察觉到制度的荒谬性而决定不遵守，公司倾向于提拔不称职的员工。
  • Hierarchical defoliation: to avoid workers perceiving the absurdity of the system and deciding not to comply, the company favours the promotion of an incompetent employee.

最后位置的迹象

Signs of the last position

彼得认为，能力不足的迹象，或者说向他人和自己隐瞒能力不足的迹象，很容易察觉。这些被称为“末位迹象”：然而，它们却给人一种职业成就的假象。

According to Peter, the signs of incompetence, or the signs of hiding incompetence from others and oneself, are easy to detect. These are called ‘signs of the last position’: however, they give the illusion of professional fulfilment.

  • 阶级癖：源自希腊语“classis”（意为“类别”或“阶级”），这是一种对分类的不必要的痴迷，以使（他们自己）产生他们正在做重要工作的错觉。
  • Classophilia: from the Greek word ‘classis’ (meaning ‘category’ or ‘class’), this is an unnecessary obsession with classification to give (themselves) the illusion that they are doing important work.
  • 巨人症白板：指无能的员工，却想占据最大的办公室。
  • Gigantism tabula: refers to the incompetent employee who wants the biggest office.
  • 纸屑狂热症：源自希腊语“Papyros”（“纸”）和拉丁语“mania”（“疯狂”或“痴迷”），指的是不称职的员工，他将文件堆积在办公桌上（因此显得杂乱无章），给人一种他非常忙碌的印象。
  • Papyromania: from the Greek word ‘Papyros’ (‘paper’) and the Latin word ‘mania’ (‘madness’ or ‘obsession’), this is a sign of an incompetent employee who piles up paperwork – hence the apparent disorder – on his desk to give the impression that he is extremely busy.
  • 纸质恐惧症（Papyrophobia）：源于希腊语“papyros”（纸）和“phobos”（恐惧症），指员工能力不足，无法容忍工作场所出现任何纸张。如果办公室井然有序，同事、上司，甚至员工本人，都会认为工作效率很高。
  • Papyrophobia: from the Greek words ‘papyros’ (‘paper’) and ‘phobos’ (‘phobia’), is a sign of an incompetent employee who cannot tolerate any paper in their workspace. If the office is organised, colleagues, superiors, and perhaps even the employee himself, will believe that work is being done efficiently.
  • 恋音癖（Phonophilia）：源于希腊语“phone”（意为“声音”）和“philos”（意为“朋友”），这是一种无能的表现，例如将自己与同事和下属的联系疏忽大意，并在办公室里安装多部电话和录音机。由于这一概念最早出现于1969年，因此根据当前的技术水平，或许应该重新表述这一“迹象”。
  • Phonophilia: from the Greek words ‘phone’ (‘voice’) and ‘philos’ (‘friend’), this is a sign of incompetence which involves blaming a lack of contact with colleagues and subordinates and installing multiple phones and tape recorders in the office. Since this idea first appeared in 1969, this ‘sign’ should probably be rephrased based on current technologies.
  • Rigor Cartis：源自拉丁语，表示对图形、图表和图表的强烈兴趣，给人一种可以控制局面的错觉。
  • Rigor Cartis: of Latin origin, this indicates an obsessive interest in graphics, diagrams and charts that give the illusion of control over situations.
  • 首字母缩写癖：源于拉丁语“sigla”（意为“标记”或“缩写”）和“mania”（意为“疯狂”或“痴迷”），指能力不足的员工会用难以理解的首字母缩写词与非专业人士交谈，以此营造出一种专业化的印象。他会把事情复杂化，因为他乐于享受由此带来的显赫地位。
  • Initial siglomania: from the Latin words ‘sigla’ (meaning ‘markings’ or ‘abbreviations’) and ‘mania’ (meaning ‘madness’ or ‘obsession’), this is a sign where the incompetent employee will speak using incomprehensible initials and acronyms with non-initiated staff, to give the impression of professionalism. He will complicate things as he takes pleasure in the importance this gives him.
  • 结构主义：源自拉丁语“structure”（“安排”、“构造”）和希腊语“philos”（“朋友”），这涉及享受在某种结构中工作，表现出这种迹象的无能员工会痴迷于他所工作的建筑物的秩序和维护，而忽略了享受工作本身。
  • Structurophilia: from the Latin word ‘structure’ (‘arrangement’, ‘construction’) and the Greek ‘philos’ (‘friend’), this involves enjoying work in a certain structure, the incompetent employee that shows evidence of this sign will be obsessed with the order and maintenance of the building where he works, to the detriment of enjoying the work itself.
  • 慌乱综合症：不称职的员工很少做出决定，并让他们等待很长时间才得到处理。
  • Flutter syndrome: the incompetent employee rarely makes decisions and allows them to wait a long time before being processed.
  • 异常的 tabula：源自拉丁语“tabula”（“盘子”或“桌子”），这是员工使用不寻常且奇怪的办公设备的表现。
  • Abnormal tabula: from the Latin word ‘tabula’ (‘plate’ or ‘table’), this is a sign of incompetence where the employee uses unusual and strange office equipment.

然而，彼得也补充说明，幸运的是，为了我们政治、社会和经济模式的正常运转，所有位于顶层的职位并不一定都由能力不足的员工占据。事实上，在对这一原则的阐释中，他强调了这样一个事实：一个组织的层级结构往往过于狭窄，以至于所有有能力的人都无法充分发挥其潜力——尽管这并非什么大问题，否则他们就会遭受层级结构的瓦解。然而，值得注意的是，有能力的上级通常会被更大的组织挖走，在那里他们能够再次晋升，直到达到他们能力不足的水平。

However, Peter qualifies his statements by explaining that, fortunately for the functioning of our political, social and economic models, all positions at the top of the hierarchy are not necessarily occupied by incompetent employees. In fact, in this clarification of the principle, he highlights the fact that the hierarchical structure of an organisation is often too small for all of the competent people – although this is not too big a fault, as otherwise they would suffer from hierarchical defoliation – to reach their potential. Nonetheless, note that the competent superiors are often headhunted by larger organisations where they are once again able to move up until they too reach their level of incompetence.

限制和扩展

Limitations and extensions

局限性和批评

Limitations and criticisms

一旦考虑到该模型所基于的假设，其局限性就显而易见了。

The limits of the model are obvious as soon as one considers the hypotheses that it is based on.

  • 如今，组织结构往往不像彼得所描述的金字塔结构那样简单。大多数情况下，协调他人的员工都没有晋升。各部门之间至少在理论上是平等的。权力下放和授权受到鼓励，并且存在着减少垂直层级结构的趋势。这种现象被称为“金字塔扁平化”。或许，这正是当代避免“彼得原理”影响的方法之一，而彼得原理源于等级制度更为僵化的时代？
  • At the moment, an organisation is often not as simple as the pyramid structure described by Peter. Most of the time, an employee who coordinates others has not been promoted. The various departments are on equal footing, at least in theory. Decentralisation and empowerment are encouraged and there is a tendency to reduce the straightforward vertical hierarchy. This phenomenon is called ‘the flattening of the pyramids’. Perhaps it is precisely one of the contemporary ways to avoid the effects of the Peter Principle which originate from a time when hierarchy was more rigid?
  • 职位不再被冻结。如果一个不称职的员工被任命到某个职位，却不承担其职责，那么该职位的许多职能很可能会逐渐被分配到其他职位。
  • A position is no longer frozen. If an incompetent employee is appointed to a position and does not assume its responsibilities, it is likely that many of the functions will be progressively assigned to another position.
  • 激励问题也成问题，因为员工展现的一些技能可能源于此。事实上，员工在某个层级上可能效率高，部分原因就在于激励。如果他能保持这种热情，就更有可能更容易地掌握新职位所需的新技能，从而提高效率。
  • The issue of motivation is also problematic, since some skills shown by the worker can come from this. Indeed, the employee may be efficient at one level of the hierarchy, partially due to motivation. If he continues this enthusiasm he is likely to acquire the new skills required for the new position more easily, making him more efficient.
  • 当前的人员流动情况令人印象深刻，因为据估计，进入劳动力市场的年轻人可能会更换其职能或业务约五次。
  • The current realities of turnover are impressive, since it is estimated that a young person entering the labour market is likely to change their function or business approximately five times.
  • 最后，最值得质疑的彼得假说无疑是：一个职位上展现的能力本质上独立于其在先前职位上所证明的能力。其他研究人员，例如意大利物理学家亚历山德罗·普鲁奇诺 (Alessandro Pluchino)、安德烈亚·拉皮萨尔达 (Andrea Rapisarda) 和社会学家切萨雷·加罗法洛 (Cesare Garofalo)，在他们的文章《彼得原理再探：一项计算研究》中，通过提出相反的假说，重新审视了这一著名原理。他们称之为“常识假说”：较高职位上的能力取决于较低职位上展现的能力，并且会增加或减少约 10%。
  • Finally, certainly the most questionable Peter hypothesis is that the competency shown in one position is inherently independent from the competency proved in a previous position. Other researchers, such as the Italian physicists Alessandro Pluchino, Andrea Rapisarda, and sociologist Cesare Garofalo in their article The Peter Principle Revisited: A Computational Study, offer a revisited perspective of the famous principle by stating the opposite hypothesis. They call it ‘the common sense hypothesis’: competency in a higher position depends on the competency shown in a lower position and is increased or decreased by approximately 10%.

彼得提出的无能实证检验方法也可能不可靠。事实上，这些症状包括如此多不同的行为，以至于我们不能像某些人那样，将它们用作彼得原理的所谓证据。如果我们考虑某些假设的表面价值，最终会面临这样的情况：太喜欢组织或过于权威的人是无能的，但组织性不够或缺乏权威的人也是无能的。如果过度总是一件坏事，那么大多数所谓的症状最初都可以被视为品质。此外，这是否就是无能员工采取这些态度（但走向极端）以试图掩盖其无能的原因。总而言之，彼得原理是无法验证的，他在作品中使用的讽刺语气表明它并没有真正的科学依据。

The empirical testing of incompetence developed by Peter can also be unreliable. Indeed, the symptoms include so many different behaviours that we cannot, as some do, use them as supposed proof of the Peter Principle. If we consider the face value of certain hypotheses, we will eventually be confronted with situations such as this: the person who likes organisation too much or is too authoritative is incompetent, but the person who is not organised enough or is not authoritative is also incompetent. If excess is always a bad thing, the majority of the alleged symptoms can originally be perceived as qualities. Also, is it the reason why an incompetent employee adopts these attitudes – but to the extreme – to try to hide his incompetence. In conclusion, the Peter Principle is unverifiable and the satirical tone he uses in his work suggests that it has no real scientific claim.

相关模型和扩展

Related models and extensions

彼得原理是一系列类似“定律”的一部分，风格或多或少有些幽默，它们以某种愤世嫉俗的口吻描述企业界，其科学严谨性并非其最关注的方面。然而，其中一些定律指出了大多数组织必须有效应对的挑战性现实。

The Peter Principle is part of a set of ‘laws’ of the same type, of a more or less humorous style, which describe the corporate world with a certain cynicism and whose scientific rigour is not its biggest concern. However, some of them point out the challenging realities with which most organisations must effectively cope.

帕金森定律

Parkinson’s Law

其中，尤其值得一提的是英国历史学家西里尔·诺斯科特·帕金森（Cyril Northcote Parkinson，1909-1993）于1955年提出的帕金森定律（Parkinson's Law）。该定律指出，工作总是会分散开来，以填满负责人的可用时间。由此推论，我们可以想象，所有可用于项目的资源都会被利用，无论是时间、金钱、人力等等。这条定律有两个基本结论：

Among these, in particular there is Parkinson’s Law (1955), from the British historian Cyril Northcote Parkinson (1909-1993), which states that the work is always spread out in order to fill the time available to the person in charge of the work. By extension, we can imagine that all available resources for are project are used, whether they are time, money, manpower, etc. There are two consequences underpin this law:

  • 增加下属。如果员工未能完成项目，他只有两个选择：要么将部分工作交给可能成为潜在竞争对手的人，要么请求下属的支持。大多数情况下，人们会选择第二种选择，首先是为了保住自己的地位，其次是为了提升自己的重要性。需要注意的是，他会确保自己有多位下属，以便分担每项任务。这样，由于没有人能够完成整个任务，就不会有人成为潜在的竞争对手。
  • Increase of subordinates. If an employee fails to complete a project, he only has two options: he can either unload a portion of the work by giving it to someone who could become a potential rival, or he can request the support of his subordinates. In most cases, the second option is chosen, firstly to protect his position and secondly to increase his importance. It should be noted that he will ensure he has several subordinates, so as to share each task. That way, since none of them are able to perform the whole task, no one will become a potential rival.
  • 工作量增加。无论是与同级还是下级共事，当多人协作时，工作量都会增加。协调任务所需的时间通常与完成工作所需的时间一样多。由于团队中几乎总会有人难以授权并承担更多责任，最终工作量会自行调整，达到一个人单独完成的水平。最终，要完成与单人完成的相同工作量，需要整个团队的共同努力，并花费额外的时间来协调所有这些人。
  • Increase of workload. Whether working with equals or subordinates, the fact is that when there are several people working, the workload increases. It often takes as much time to coordinate the task as it does to do the work. As there is almost always someone in the team who has trouble delegating and takes on more responsibility, the work will rectify itself in the end to match what one person could have produced alone. Ultimately, to produce the same work – as only one person would have produced – it takes a whole team dedicated to it and additional time was spent coordinating all of these people.

呆伯特原则

The Dilbert Principle

我们还会提到“呆伯特原理”，它源自斯科特·亚当斯（美国漫画家，生于1957年）的同名漫画。根据他的说法，即使不称职的员工从未展现过任何特殊技能，他们也会立即获得晋升并成为管理者。这一原理比彼得原理更为激进，因为它假设我们有意将管理职能委托给不称职的员工，这样他们就不会造成任何损害。当然，这假设管理永远是无用的。

We will also mention the Dilbert Principle, derived from an eponymous comic strip by Scott Adams (American cartoonist, born in 1957). According to him, the incompetent employees are immediately promoted and become managers, even if they have never shown any special skills. This principle is even more radical than the Peter Principle, since it assumes that we consciously entrust management functions to incompetent employees so that they cannot cause any damage. This, of course, assumes that management is always useless.

同样，我们可以引用那句流行的说法：“能者做，不能者教”。

Similarly, we can cite the popular saying that “those who can, do; those who can’t, teach”.

虽然我们不能称它们为“模型”——因为它们并非科学——但这些原则在经验上对经济模型的理论表现表现出一定的阻力。我们是否应该放弃这些模型——尽管我们在现实中知道它们的局限性——并考虑随意晋升？

Although we cannot call them ‘models’ as such – because they are not scientific – these principles show some empirical resistance to the theoretical performance of economic models. Should we give up on these models – the limits of which we know in reality – and consider granting promotions at random?

实际应用

Practical application

彼得原理发挥作用的案例研究既众多又不存在。案例众多，是因为我们每个人都能轻易想象出这样一种情形：一位不称职的员工得到提拔，并在同事或上司身上发现了彼得所描述的迹象。至于说这些迹象真的证明了员工的无能，那就是另一回事了。衡量员工的绩效非常困难，大多数人力资源经理也深知这一点。同样，员工也常常认为上司无能，因为批评别人比承担责任更容易。大多数时候，文献中提到的声称员工无能的案例，都不过是彼得原理支持者的臆想。从这个意义上说，真正的案例并不存在。

The case studies where the Peter Principle is at work are both numerous and non-existent at the same time. They are numerous, since each of us easily manages to imagine a situation where an incompetent employee is promoted, recognising the signs described by Peter among our colleagues or superiors. As for saying that they actually prove incompetence, that is another matter. It is quite difficult, and most human resource managers know this well, to measure the performance of an employee. Similarly, employees will often tend to find their superior incompetent because it is easier to criticise others than to take responsibility. Most of the time, literature presents cases where incompetence is claimed, but comes from little more than the imagination of Peter Principle supporters. In this sense, real case examples are non-existent.

卡塔尼亚研究

Study of Catania

亚历山德罗·普鲁奇诺（Alessandro Pluchino）、安德烈亚·拉皮萨尔达（Andrea Rapisarda）和切萨雷·加罗法洛（Cesare Garofalo）在他们的文章《彼得原理再探：一项计算研究》中，并没有讲述轶事，而是尝试用不同的方式在现实中运用该模型。他们通过改变晋升假设，用计算机模拟了金字塔结构的演变。他们的文章揭示了惊人的发现，并因此获得了搞笑诺贝尔经济学奖——该奖项是对诺贝尔奖的戏仿，旨在奖励那些最不寻常的研究。然而，他们的研究仍然非常严肃，其结果的奇特性强化了彼得提出的思考和幽默假设。

Instead of telling anecdotes, Alessandro Pluchino, Andrea Rapisarda and Cesare Garofalo, in their article The Peter Principle Revisited: A Computational Study, preferred to try a different way of tackling the model in reality. They used a computer simulation of the evolution of the pyramid structure by varying the hypotheses of promotion. Their article revealed astonishing findings, earning them an Ig Nobel Prize in Economics, a parody of the Nobel Prize that rewards the most unusual research. However, their study is nevertheless very serious and the bizarre nature of the results reinforces the thinking and humorous hypotheses developed by Peter.

虚构组织的定义

Definition of a fictitious organisation

因此，他们使用 Netlogo（一种专门为多智能体模拟而设计的编程语言，用于测试博弈论的不同方面）在计算机程序中创建了一个虚拟组织，该组织由六个层级组成（分别包含 81、41、21、11、5 和 1 个智能体）。每个智能体的年龄范围为 18 至 60 岁，技能等级为 1 至 10。

Therefore, they created, on a computer program (using Netlogo, a programming language specifically designed for conducive multi-agent simulation to test different aspects of game theory), a fictitious organisation made up of six hierarchical levels (containing 81, 41, 21, 11, 5 and 1 agents respectively). Each agent is characterised by an age ranging from 18 to 60 and a skill level from 1 to 10.

在模拟开始时，年龄和技能水平是根据上面描述的统计分布随机确定的。

At the beginning of the simulation, ages and skills levels are randomly determined on the basis of the statistical distribution described above.

“正态”统计分布

‘Normal’ statistical distribution

统计分布给出接近平均结果（在图表上任意设置为0）的概率很高，而当我们试图得到远离顶部或底部的结果时，概率会越来越低。这被认为是最能描述大样本现实的概率形式，根据定义，我们发现的平均事件远多于异常事件。

A statistical distribution gives a strong probability of near-average results – arbitrarily set to 0 on the chart – and an increasingly low probability as we try to get a result that moves away from the top or the bottom. This is considered to be the form of chance that best describes the reality of large samples and, by definition, we find far more average events than exceptional events.

模拟

Simulation

一旦初始情况建立，模拟即可开始。在游戏的每一轮中，代理的年龄都会增加。达到 60 岁的代理会消失，空缺的代理会通过提升较低级别的代理来填补。最低级别的空缺则通过添加新代理来填补，新代理的年龄和技能是随机确定的。

Once the initial situation is established, the simulation can begin. In each round of the game, the age of the agents is increased. Each agent who reaches 60 disappears and the gaps are filled by promoting agents from the lower levels. The gaps in the lowest level are filled by adding new agents whose ages and skills are determined randomly.

当代理人改变级别时，他的能力也会根据两个经过检验的假设而改变：

When an agent changes level, his competence also changes according to the two tested hypotheses:

  • 彼得假说。新的能力水平完全是随机的。
  • The Peter hypothesis. The new level of competence is completely random.
  • 常识假设。新的能力水平与之前的水平相比，最多增加或减少10%。
  • The common sense hypothesis. The new level of competence shows a maximum 10% increase or decrease compared with the previous level.

在这两种情况下，都需要衡量系统的整体绩效，这对应于所有层级的平均绩效。需要注意的是，员工的晋升越高，其个人绩效也应该越高。

In both cases, it is necessary to measure the overall performance of the system, which corresponds to the average performance of all levels. Note that the more an employee climbs the ladder, the more his individual performance should increase.

当然，研究人员面临的问题与任何管理者面临的问题都是一样的：谁应该晋升？针对每个假设，研究人员测试了三种晋升类型：

Naturally, the question facing researchers is the same one that faces any manager: who should be promoted? For each hypothesis, the researchers tested three types of promotion:

  • 提拔最优秀的员工；
  • promoting the best employee;
  • 提拔最不称职的员工；
  • promoting the most incompetent employee;
  • 提拔一名随机选择的员工。
  • promoting a randomly selected employee.

结果

Results

很快，系统性能就达到了平衡点。

Very quickly, the performance of the system reached a point of equilibrium.

根据常识假设，这并不令人意外。提拔最优秀的人才会带来良好的整体绩效，而提拔能力不足的人才则会导致整体绩效不佳。随机晋升不会对整体绩效产生重大影响。

Under the common sense hypothesis, there is no real surprise. A good overall performance is achieved when the best people are promoted and a poor overall performance when incompetent people are promoted. Random promotion does not have a major impact on overall performance.

另一方面，如果我们考察彼得假说，就会得出一个令人惊讶的结论——与搞笑诺贝尔奖得主意大利研究人员的发现截然相反——那就是我们必须提拔不称职的员工。事实上，如果将一名能力较差的员工调升到更高的级别，他很有可能会被更优秀的人取代，因为大多数员工的水平都很平庸。此外，通过重新分配，这些能力较差的员工的表现将被“重演”，再次随机抽取，很有可能再次获得平均水平。即使抽取的结果不好，他仍然会进入下一轮。因此，提拔最不称职的员工是彼得假说的合理结论。然后，与常识假说一样，机会仍然是中性的。至于最优秀员工的晋升，其运作方式正如彼得所描述的那样：它会将每个人推向不称职的水平，从而导致整体绩效低下。

On the other hand, if we look at the Peter hypothesis, a surprising conclusion – which is the opposite of that found by the Ig Nobel-winning Italian researchers – is clear: we must promote the incompetent employees. Indeed, if you move a poor worker to a higher level, there is a good chance he will be replaced by someone better than him, the majority of agents being average. In addition to this, the performance of the poor workers will be ‘replayed’, randomly drawn again, through his reassignment, with a good chance of getting an average result once again. And if the chance results in a bad outcome, he will still proceed to the next round. Thus, promoting the most incompetent employees is the logical conclusion in the Peter hypothesis. Then, as is the case of the common sense hypothesis, chance remains neutral. As for the promotion of the best employees, it works exactly as Peter described: it propels everyone to their level of incompetence, making the overall performance defective.

结论

Conclusion

因此，要么彼得是对的，我们只能建议管理人员提拔最差的员工，要么我们接受更高级别的能力只是较低级别能力的简单变体，而提拔最优秀的员工仍然是首选的解决方案。

Therefore, either Peter is right and we can only advise managers to promote the worst employees, or we accept that competence at a higher level is a simple variation of competence at lower levels and promoting the best workers remains the preferred solution.

建议

Advice

总的来说，彼得处理这个问题的方式过于静态和简单。为什么特定职位的能力应该被视为一个常数？如果现有的人力资源管理体系有效，监管绩效评估之后应该进行官员访谈和员工培训，以提高他们的工作效率。

Overall, Peter approaches the problem in too static and simplistic a manner. Why should the competence for a given position be considered a constant? If the human resource management system in place is effective, regulatory performance measures should be followed by interviews with officials and staff training to increase the efficiency of their work.

当然，这也有几个缺点：

Of course, this presents several disadvantages:

  • 首先，我们需要相关的关键绩效指标，以便尽可能客观地评估工作质量。例如，对于销售人员来说，只需衡量进入商店的潜在客户数量（越来越多的商店为此安装了传感器）、销售人员的销售额以及两者之间的关系就足够了。然而，在衡量公务员或办公室职员的工作质量时，绩效计算的风险更大。彼得本人在谈到能力不足时，给人的印象是，这种能力不足更多是基于普遍的感受，而不是具体的指标。
  • Firstly, we need relevant key performance indicators to determine the quality of work as objectively as possible. In the case of a seller, would be sufficient, for example, to simply measure the number of potential customers who entered the store (more and more shops are installing sensors for this purpose), the amount collected by the seller and the relationship between the two. However, the calculation of performance is more risky when it comes to measuring the quality of work produced by a civil servant or an office worker. Peter himself, when speaking of incompetence, gives the impression that it is based more on a widespread feeling than on specific indicators.
  • 其次，有效的人力资源系统和培训比简单地衡量员工绩效并根据过去的经验直接提拔合适的员工更难实施，而且成本更高。
  • Secondly, an effective human resource system and training are more difficult to implement and more expensive than simply measuring employee performance and directly promoting the right employee based on past experience.

无论彼得假说是否正确，管理者可能会以两种相反的方式考虑层级结构：

Whether the Peter hypothesis is true or not, managers may consider the hierarchy in two opposite ways:

  • 如果每个职能以及与之相关的技能都被明确定义，那么实施关键绩效指标和评估绩效就会简单得多；
  • if each function and the skills related to it are clearly defined, it is much simpler to implement key performance indicators and assess performance;
  • 相反，如果对于每个员工必须执行的任务故意留下一些不确定性，那么就更容易让员工摆脱一些他不胜任的任务，但这对效率有相当大的影响。
  • if, on the contrary, some uncertainty is deliberately left regarding the tasks that each employee must carry out, it is much easier to relieve a worker of some of the tasks for which he is not competent, but this has a considerable impact on efficiency.

此外，通过消除棘轮效应，可以提高员工的流动性。降职现象比彼得想象的更为常见。

Moreover, it is possible to make workers more mobile by removing the ratchet effect. Demotions are more common than Peter seems to believe.

当彼得假说不成立时

When the Peter hypothesis does not hold

如果彼得假说不成立，那么组织通常设立的常识性制度——即提拔最优秀员工——就完全有效了。它具有双重优势：一方面激励员工为了晋升而努力表现，另一方面又能为组织节省培训费用，因为他们会竭尽全力获得更高职位所需的技能。

If the Peter hypothesis is not verified, then the common sense system – which involves promoting the best workers – usually set up by organisations if fully efficient. It has the double advantage of motivating employees to scramble to perform better in the hope of getting a promotion, saving the organisation money on training, as they themselves will make every effort to acquire the skill level required for the superior position.

当彼得假说成立时

When the Peter hypothesis holds true

另一方面，如果“彼得假说”被证明成立，问题就更大了。如果提拔最不称职的员工，应该谨慎行事，以免打击员工积极性。此外，还必须注重财务激励，避免将晋升制度作为奖励。

On the other hand, it is much more problematic if the Peter hypothesis proves to be true. If the most incompetent workers are promoted, this should be done discreetly due to the risk of demotivating employees. It is also necessary to focus on financial incentives and refrain from using the promotions system as a reward.

这种考虑和给予晋升的方式有其局限性，因为它会给组织带来巨大的成本，而且无法找到最适合该职位的人。

This way of considering and giving promotions has its limitations, since it generates significant costs for the organisation and does not find the person best suited for the position.

最后，如果彼得假说符合组织的现实，并且棘轮效应如他所认为的那样固定不变，那么唯一真正的解决方案就是尽可能有效地支持员工，衡量所需技能，激励他们并进行培训。相比于仅靠员工之间的竞争就能让他们胜任各个层级的工作，这给组织带来的成本要高得多。

Finally, if the Peter hypothesis corresponds to the reality of the organisations and the ratchet effect is as fixed as he believes, the only real solution is to support employees as effectively as possible by measuring the skills needed, motivating them and training them. This costs the organisation much more than if the only competition experienced between employees made them competent at all levels of the hierarchy.

概括

Summary

  • 劳伦斯·J·彼得 (Laurence J. Peter) 和雷蒙德·赫尔 (Raymond Hull) 提出的这一原则出现在 1969 年的讽刺作品《彼得原理》中，当时企业面临着稳定和经济健全的环境，其目标是实现结构的增长和发展，因此不可避免地会进行促销管理。
  • The principle developed by Laurence J. Peter and Raymond Hull appears in a satirical work entitled The Peter Principle from 1969, a time when businesses, facing a stable and economically sound environment, targeted the growth and development of their structure and therefore inevitably managed promotions.
  • 该原则基于以下假设：所有组织都会提拔有能力的员工，直到他们达到无法胜任工作且无法被撤职的职位；因此，该组织会走向普遍的无能。
  • The principle is based on the following hypothesis: all organisations promote competent employees until they reach a position in which they cannot perform competently and from which they cannot be removed; the organisation therefore moves towards widespread incompetence.
  • 贡献主要在于管理者，他们需要了解如何管理员工的流动，从而提高组织的整体绩效。为此，他们应该确保技能和集体智慧的发展，因为没有人是完美的，但团队可以完美。
  • The contribution lies mainly with managers who need to know how to manage the movements of their staff in order to improve the overall performance of their organisation. They should, to that end, ensure the development of skills and collective intelligence, because no one is perfect, but a team can be.
  • 该模型的假设引起了争议，尤其是声称新职位所需的技能并不依赖于之前职位所需的技能的假​​设。
  • The hypotheses of the model cause controversy, particularly the hypothesis that claims the skills required for a new position are not dependent on those seen in the previous position.
  • 其他定律，包括帕金森定律（该定律指出组织最终会变得无效），都与彼得原理有相同的倾向。
  • Other laws, including Parkinson’s Law on the natural tendency of organisations to eventually become ineffective, lean in the same direction as the Peter Principle.
  • 建议：
    • 如果彼得假说不成立，就依靠常识，提拔最优秀的员工；
    • 如果彼得假说成立：
  • Advice:
    • if the Peter hypothesis does not hold, rely on common sense and promote the best employees;
    • if the Peter hypothesis holds true:
  • 秘密提拔最差的员工；
  • promote the worst employees without making it known;
  • 在不改变员工角色的情况下给予财务激励；
  • give financial incentives without changing the employees’ role;
  • 单独观察每个员工并在同一层级内操作动作。
